<HEADLINE>
AMERICAN AIRLINES, UNION NEGOTIATE DEBT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DAN REED 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ The board of American Airlines' pilots union
is considering proposals that could erase the labor group's $45.5
million debt to the carrier in exchange for changes to the current
contract, sources familiar with the discussions said Wednesday
night.
</P>
