<P>
   IMMIG-LABOR-RIGHTS (Undated) _ The Equal Employment Opportunity
Commission announced this week that it would for the first time
extend broad anti-discrimination rights to illegal immigrants to
protect them if employers fire them or otherwise discriminate
against them because of their race, sex, age or religion. By Steven
Greenhouse.
</P>
<P>
   HOTDOG-RECALL (New York) _ Food-safety inspectors are exploring
whether several recent deaths were caused by contaminated
frankfurters that were produced at a Bronx processing plant, and
the products have been recalled in at least 21 states. In a
national advisory to health officials, the Centers for Disease
Control and Prevention said that it was investigating whether two
deaths, and five illnesses, were caused by listeria from hot dogs
made at the plant. The cases occurred in Minnesota, Wisconsin,
Georgia and Rhode Island. By Katherine E. Finkelstein.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CAMPAIGN _ (Moved in ``p'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   REPUBS-SOCSEC _ Earl Pomeroy, D-N.D., has been one of his
party's strongest voices for protecting Social Security. So he
finds it particularly galling that he is one of seven Democrats
under attack in a Republican ad campaign that accuses the Democrats
in the House of raiding Social Security. He complains that a year
before the election, things are already on a campaign footing. And
that is just the point. After years of being clobbered by Democrats
in the annual budget fight, Republicans are aggressively aiming at
the next election, and seem to battling the Democrats to a draw. By
Alison Mitchell.
</P>
<P>
   FORBES-MONEY (Undated) _ The sheer size of Steve Forbes'
financial holdings _ and the private way he turns them into
campaign cash _ makes them difficult to scrutinize and turns the
traditional way of looking at campaign finance on its head. By
Leslie Wayne.
