<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-28 11:43 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1080 &Cx1f; tad-z
r s BC-FBN-MANNING29-COX     10-28 0867
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-MANNING29-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Colts' Manning says he strives to be like Aikman
 &HT;    By Rick Cantu
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ After Peyton Manning finishes his career 10 or
12 years from now, after he smashes dozens of NFL passing records,
after he etches his name in history as one of the greatest
quarterbacks ever, he wants to be compared favorably with one man.
</P>
<P>
   Troy Aikman.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman represents everything that Manning strives to be with the
Indianapolis Colts. Aikman probably will never set any meaningful
league passing marks, but three Super Bowl rings have established
him as a champion in Manning's 23-year-old eyes.
</P>
<P>
   ``For any young quarterback coming into the game, Troy Aikman's
career is the one you want to have,'' Manning said Wednesday. ``He
was a No. 1 draft pick, just like me. Troy is in the game for the
long haul. And both of us struggled in our first seasons.''
</P>
<P>
   Aikman and Manning will meet for the first time Sunday afternoon
at the RCA Dome. The Dallas-Indianapolis game will showcase the
past and future of the NFL.
</P>
<P>
   It is only natural to compare Aikman and Manning. When Aikman
was drafted in 1989, the Cowboys were 1-15, and he was injured
during the team's only victory, over Washington. Manning fared only
slightly better as a rookie, leading the Colts to a 3-13 record
last year.
</P>
<P>
   ``Yeah, and how long did it take before Troy and the Cowboys won
a Super Bowl?'' Manning said. The Cowboys won the 1993 Super Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys and Colts are compared regularly because each team
has been built around three kings. The Aikman-Emmitt Smith-Michael
Irvin trio is the biggest reason the Cowboys already have been
dubbed the team of the decade. In Indy, there are predictions that
the Manning-Edgerrin James-Marvin Harrison trio will rule the next
decade.
</P>
<P>
   Who's to disagree? In the latest AFC statistics, Manning ranks
third in passing, James is second in rushing and Harrison is second
in receptions. Manning is second in touchdown passes and Harrison
is first in touchdown catches.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's all built around Peyton,'' said James, a rookie running
back from Miami. ``You have to do everything around him, because
he's the one who's pulling the trigger.''
</P>
<P>
   Manning's progress is one reason the Colts might be the league's
most improved team. They are 4-2 heading into Sunday and looking to
reach the playoffs for the first time in three years.
</P>
<P>
   With Manning, James and Harrison, the Colts have a blueprint
that looks remarkably similar to the one Tom Landry and Jimmy
Johnson unfolded more than a decade ago. Irvin was Landry's final
first-round draft pick, and Johnson drafted Aikman and Smith in the
first round the next two seasons.
</P>
<P>
   The Colts' architect is team president Bill Polian, who built
the Buffalo Bills as the team's general manager in the late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
   Nobody questioned the Colts for drafting Harrison four years ago
and Manning last year. Both had solid credentials when they left
college. The addition of James this year, however, was questioned
by draft experts from coast to coast.
</P>
<P>
   The Colts unveiled a draft-day shocker by taking James over
Heisman Trophy winner Ricky Williams of Texas. Polian and
Indianapolis Coach Jim Mora were vilified by many people around the
league who believed Williams was a can't-miss superstar who would
look good in a Colts jersey.
</P>
<P>
   Polian and Mora stood their ground, saying James was ``a better
fit'' for Indy's offensive system. So far, it's hard to disagree.
James leads Williams in rushing yardage (520 to 403), passing
yardage (113 to 22) and touchdowns (four to zero). The Saints have
won just one game.
</P>
<P>
   ``Both Edgerrin and Ricky are going to be great players,''
Manning said. ``Ricky Williams is a guy who truly needs to be
featured in your offense, and that's what the Saints are doing.
Here with the Colts, we don't feature anybody.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're very balanced. We try to get the ball in our playmakers'
hands. If they're stopping one guy, we can beat you with another
guy. Edgerrin really fits that mold.''
</P>
<P>
   Manning, the only NFL quarterback to take every offensive snap
with his team last season, remains the most important piece to the
Colts' puzzle. Cowboys coaches and players said their No. 1 mission
Sunday is to contain him.
</P>
<P>
   Said Cowboys cornerback Deion Sanders: ``Peyton has a quick
release and gets rid of the ball quickly. He almost never takes a
sack. The Colts have a nice scheme for him, which allows him to do
some wonderful things.''
</P>
<P>
   One of Manning's fans will be on the other side of the field
Sunday. Aikman said he has admired Manning since the second-year
pro was at the University of Tennessee. Manning is a good
ambassador for football, on and off the field, Aikman said.
</P>
<P>
   ``I like the way Peyton handled himself last year, especially
after defeats,'' Aikman said. ``Having been through that (in 1989),
I know how difficult it can be. But I didn't expect less from him,
after watching him in college. I've always admired the way he has
handled himself and represented himself and his team, and that's
not going to change.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
