<P>
   WOULD-YOU-RATHER _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Would you rather dive
headfirst off a high diving board into an empty pool . . . or be
bungee-snapped back into a wall of needles? How about this: Would
you rather have a lisp that appears only in your writing . . . or
fizz up like Alka- Seltzer whenever you go into water? (Things to
consider: making your own Perrier, typing ``Mithithippi.'') Last
one: Would you rather have a ketchup-dispensing navel . . . or a
pencil-sharpening nostril? These are the absurd dilemmas that keep
authors Justin Heimberg and David Gomberg awake at night. Or at
least well-published. The former college roommates, who used to
pitch loaded questions at each other for sport, have just published
their second book of made-up conundrums, ``Would You Rather 2,
Electric Boogaloo?'' We have some questions of our own for them.
(Houck, Palm Beach Post). MOVED.
