<HEADER>
A1151 &Cx1f; tad-z
r t BC-GETAWAY-FESTIVALS29-C     10-28 0456
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GETAWAY-FESTIVALS29-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Southern happenings
 &HT;    By Paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  Gainesville, Ga. _ NightFall, Elachee Nature Science Center's
fall festival, is Saturday. Wear a costume, bring a flashlight and
take a hike in the Chicopee Woods Nature Preserve to learn about
spiders, bats, bears and other noctural animals from costumed
naturalists. Sip cider by a bonfire while listening to
storytellers. Also, owl program by Monteen McCord. 6-9 p.m.
770-535-1976.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Various Georgia locations _ ``Christmas Made in the South,''
featuring hundreds of artists and crafters from around the country,
will be at the Columbus Convention and Trade Center Friday through
Sunday; at the Macon Centreplex on Nov. 5-7; at the Augusta Civic
Center on Nov. 12-14; and the Savannah Civic Center on Nov. 19-21.
1-800-683-3772.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Columbus, Ga. _ The Columbus Museum presents ``Towards a New
Century: Contemporary Art from the Permanent Collection'' on view
Sunday through Jan. 23. Also current: ``Vintage Clothing From the
Permanent Collection'' through April 2 and ``Selection of Quilts
from the Permanent Collection'' through April 30. 706-649-0713.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Williamsburg, Va. _ ``Ghosts and Ghoulies: A Halloween Weekend
in Colonial Williamsburg'' Friday through Sunday includes a stay at
one of the resort hotels and a program of activities including
learning about Halloween customs, ghost stories and tours of
graveyards. Call for prices. 1-800-447-8679 or www.history.org.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  St. Augustine, Fla. _ ``Halloween Nights: Old Haunts in the
Old City'' Friday through Sunday includes participating attractions
(Ripley's Believe It or Not Museum, 3-D World, Potter's Wax Museum,
Oldest Wooden Schoolhouse and A Ghostly Experience Walking Tour).
$25 per person. Also, a free children's costume parade and trick or
treating Oct. 31. 904-471-9010.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Tampa _ Guavaween, a Latin-style Mardi Gras, is Saturday on
the streets of Ybor City. The Family Funfest (11 a.m.-3 p.m.) gives
way to the night of costumed revelry at 4 p.m. Amusement rides,
games, food, Home Depot children's workshop, trick or treating,
scavenger hunt, storytelling, contests and exhibits. 813-242-4828
or www.cc-events.org.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Blowing Rock, N.C. _ Tweetsie Railroad's nightly Halloween
Festival and Ghost Train continues through Sunday. In addition to
the haunted train ride, there will be a Haunted House, a Black
Light Show in Doc Tingle's Laboratory and Kid Zone and Creepy
Carnival for younger children. Gates open at 7:30 p.m.
1-800-526-5740 or www.tweetsie.com.
</P>
<P>
   _Paula Crouch Thrasher writes for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
