<SLUG> BC-MUSIC-SHARPS-REVIEW-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LIVING WITH LIARS INC. 
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  
(Fred Shuster's weekly ``Sharps &AMP; Flats'' music column) 
 
 
By FRED SHUSTER 
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Single-named singer-guitarist Raile of the
modern-rock band Liars Inc. says the Hollywood lifestyle almost
knocked him out of the game permanently.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was playing in a band called Dusted,'' he explained. ``Two
friends had OD'd and I was going to be the third. I finally left to
figure out what I was going to do with my life. Finally, my old
drummer came around and asked if I was ready to start another
band.''
</P>
<P>
   That project became Liars Inc., which recently released its
debut album, ``Superjaded'' (Foodchain).
</P>
<P>
   ``The name seemed to describe what my reality had become,''
Raile said. ``My life was a big lie and I was chasing the ultimate
lie. I'm not a liar today but the name still describes many aspects
of the world that surrounds us.''
</P>
<P>
   Liars Inc.'s album has attracted attention on alt-rock radio for
such catchy and aggressive tracks as ``Anybody,'' ``After I Begin''
and ``Always.''
</P>
<P>
   Raile is plainly grateful for the second chance he was given.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm very humbled now in my life,'' he said. ``Even at your
most hopeful, there's always a bit of doubt somewhere. Maybe that's
why I think people relate more to pain than happiness. I guess it's
best to just say it in the music. It's easier to say with guitars
and drums.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
A LILLYWHITE REPUTATION &QL;
</P>
<P>
   U2 producer Steve Lillywhite plays bass with Boston's Guster on
Nov. 11 at the House of Blues. Lillywhite, who produced Guster's
acclaimed ``Lost and Gone Forever'' disc, hasn't appeared on stage
in 20 years. ... Van Dyke Parks and Joe Henry will perform at noon
Saturday at Starbucks in Westwood Village. KCRW's Mike Morrison
will host. ... Michael Schelle, author of ``The Score,'' a
behind-the-scenes look at 15 film composers including John Barry
and Elmer Bernstein, will sign copies of the book at 7 p.m.
Thursday at Samuel French Bookshop in Studio City. Christopher
Young, whose composing credits include ``Hellraiser,'' ``Species''
and ``Murder in the First,'' will join Schelle. ... Bonnie Raitt
was the third recipient of the B.B. King Blues Hero Award,
established in 1997 to recognize an artist whose career has been
characterized by community service and charitable activity. &QL; 
___ &QL;
</P>
<P>
   To reach music writer Fred Shuster with tips or comments, e-mail
him at dnlalalife(at)aol.com. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
