<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL &LR;  (``i'' code)
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-SECT (Beijing) _ Falun Gong followers hold an
extraordinary clandestine news conference for a few foreign
reporters in Beijing. They appeal for international protection. By
Erik Eckholm.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-ENVOY (Washington) _ Confirmation hearing is planned
Thursday on the nomination of Adm. Joseph Prueher to be U.S.
ambassador to China, which Sen. Jesse Helms is likely to turn into
a full examination of administration policies on China. By Eric
Schmitt.
</P>
<P>
   ARMENIA-ATTACK (Moscow) _ The standoff at the Armenian
parliament ends as the gunmen who assassinated the prime minister
and others surrender and release their hostages. By Michael Wines.
</P>
<P>
   NIGERIA-U.S. (Washington) _ President Clinton meets the Nigerian
president; a joint news conference is set for mid-afternoon. By
David E. Sanger.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
