</P>
<P>
   ORE-SUICIDE (Portland, Ore.) _ Fiercely libertarian, pro states
rights Oregon resents intrusion by the federal government into its
assisted suicide law, noting the law was enacted after a referendum
that was approved by 60% of the state's voters. As the same time,
people also point out that only 15 people have taken advantage of
assisted suicide since the law was enacted in 1997. By Sam Howe
Verhovek.
</P>
