   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; ROYALS-JORDAN-INTERVIEW (Undated) _ It has been less than a
year since King Abdullah II, 37, succeeded his father, King
Hussein, after Jordan's longtime ruler died of cancec. Abdullah's
29-year-old wife, Queen Rania Al-Abdullah, was formally enthroned
six weeks later. The couple's marriage, a blend of Arab
traditionalism and Western modernism, has become something of a
blueprint for the future of their country. By Joseph Kahn. 2,400
words. Two takes. PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGE-BOARD-SHIFT (Undated) _ The College Board, for decades
associated mostly with the test that has held so much sway over
college admissions, is redefining its mission, recognizing that it
has focused too much on the SAT. By Kate Zernike. 1,200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LIFESTYLE &LR;   &UR; (l) &LR;
</P>
<P>
