<P>
   TRAIN: An engineer who probably fell asleep caused a fatal
collision involving two Union Pacific trains near Topeka, Kan., in
July 1997, federal investigators have determined; officials also
faulted the conductor, who left the engineer alone for 20 minutes
prior to the crash, as well as the railroad for not having an
effective fatigue-awareness program. Robert A. Cronkleton.
