<SLUG> BC-BUSINESS-BJT29-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE BUSINESS BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These business stories for release Friday, October 29, 1999, are
moving today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   Stories are moving in the financial (f) category. Stories also
moving in lifestyle will be marked with (f, l).
</P>
<P>
   Separate budgets move daily with spot news, features, sports and
commentary.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   SEARS _ Sears will announce today plans to expand its Great
Indoors concept, which competes with Home Depot Expo. Sears has
been testing stores in Denver and Phoenix. The first store that
competes head-to-head with Expo opens soon in Dallas. It's unlikely
that they'll open one in Atlanta, but they could go in other Depot
markets. (Bond, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   ATM-FEES _ ATLANTA _ Everyone seems to be fed up with ATM fees,
especially those charged by banks for using other banks ATMs. A
handful of states and cities, including Iowa, Connecticut and Santa
Monica, Ca., are so sick of ATMS fees they've completely banned
them. San Francisco votes on a similar measure in November. The
Pentagon is even considering abolishing ATM fees at military
bases.(Meadows, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 16.
</P>
<P>
   DELTA _ BOSTON _ Delta holds its annual meeting Thursday in
Boston. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   WAFFLE _ ATLANTA _ The cook in the Waffle House discrimination
case files his answer and counterclaim. Ron Biddy, accused to
refusing to cook food for five black plaintiffs, gives his
rambling, incoherent account of what happened. (Poole, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COX-DIGITAL _ ATLANTA _ Cox Communications continues to boost
its numbers of customers for new digital services, according to the
company's third quarter results. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COXNET BUDGET INFORMATION FOR SUBSCRIBERS OF THE NYT NEWS
