<P>
   FRISCO-MAYOR (San Francisco) _ Mayors all over the country are
sailing the friendly waters of prosperity. But despite a booming
economy, low unemployment and plunging crime rates that mirror the
trend across the nation, voters in politically obsessed San
Francisco are not happy. San Franciscans are notoriously hard to
please, ousting the last two mayors after single terms, but Willie
Lewis Brown Jr., who entered office as Mr. San Francisco, as
colorful and irrepressible as the city considers itself, has
disappointed voters on all sides. By Evelyn Nieves.
</P>
