<SLUG> BC-HALLOWEEN-EASY-COSTUMES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HAUTE COSTUMES RIGHT FROM THE CLOSET 
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  
By BARBARA DE WITT 
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The apples are bobbing, the brew is bubbling, and the bewitching
hour is almost here.
</P>
<P>
   You still don't have a Halloween costume?
</P>
<P>
   Quit whining about how dumb costume parties are. And don't
complain that all the good costumes were already sold when you got
to the store.
</P>
<P>
   Just scare up something out of your closet and have a happy
Halloween.
</P>
<P>
   Yeah, right there between your new work suits and old sweaters
is a haute Halloween ensemble just waiting to party. And we don't
mean a sheet with holes for your eyes and nose. Besides, with all
the designer sheets these days, it's hard to find a ghostly white
one without lace trim.
</P>
<P>
   Think you can't pull it off in time? Take a gander at some
costume ideas that Daily News staffers came up with:
</P>
<P>
   _ Mummy: Wrap yourself with old white rags, strips of sheets or
a white tablecloth, and accent with gauze. Get a bit muddy and walk
with a limp, dragging one arm.
</P>
<P>
   _ Traffic signal: Wear a black top and pants and pin, sew or
tape a circle of red, yellow and green fabric on your chest. Felt
is best, but even colored paper will work.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gypsy: Start with a long, full skirt. Add scarves, big
earrings, stacks of bracelets, an anklet, and rings on each finger.
If your hair isn't long and wavy, wrap a scarf around it and tie in
the back with the ends hanging down your back.
</P>
<P>
   _ Cowboy: Jeans, a plaid shirt, cowboy boots and hat are the key
ingredients. No plaid shirt? Try a white T-shirt and a denim
jacket, accented with a bandanna scarf tied around your neck or a
bolo tie left over from the '80s. Also check your accessories
drawer for a western-themed belt to complete the ensemble. That
beaded souvenir belt from Colorado will do.
</P>
<P>
   _ Movie star: Get yourself glammed up with a slinky gown and a
fur or feather boa to drag behind you. Add dark glasses and strike
a pose.
</P>
<P>
   _ Fashion maven: Go as a New York fashion plate in all black (or
navy) with a gold chain belt from the '80s, and three watches on
one wrist (for L.A., New York and Paris). Big black-and-gold
glasses are a nice touch, especially if they have a designer label.
Carry a fashion mag under your arm or sticking out of a black tote
bag.
</P>
<P>
   _ Farmer: Overalls, hiking boots and a colorful hanky sticking
out of your back pocket.
</P>
<P>
   _ Columbo: Rumple your hair, chew on a cigar butt, and wear a
tan trench coat that you've rolled up and stepped on before
wearing.
</P>
<P>
   _ Mickey Mouse: Start with a black turtleneck and black tights.
Add red shorts and suspenders, if you've got them. Then paint your
nose black and add your mouse ears from Disneyland.
</P>
<P>
   _ Fat cat: Wear a man's white dress shirt, with pillow
underneath, stuffed into pants. Then pin a pair of black leggings
on the back as a tail. Paint whiskers on face with black eyeliner,
stick a cigar in your pocket or mouth, and stuff fake (or real)
dollars in between the buttons on your shirt.
</P>
<P>
   _ Grapes: If you're like a lot of families, you've got a stash
of balloons. Hopefully you've got a bunch of purple, red or green
balloons that can be blown up and taped on a black body suit.
</P>
<P>
   _ Freudian slip: Wear a black slip with the words ID, EGO, SUPER
EGO spelled out in silver glitter. Sheer black stockings, sexy
sandals and a boa complete the look.
</P>
<P>
   _ Miss Scarlet: Wear last year's Chinese print sheath, flutter a
fan, and go as the mysterious Miss Scarlet who is a suspect in the
who-dunnit game of Clue. Or, if you're a ``Gone With the Wind''
fan, dress up as Scarlett O'Hara in a white dress with an emerald
green ribbon around the waist, pinch your cheeks, and talk with a
southern drawl.
</P>
<P>
   _ Magnum, P.I.: Got a Hawaiian shirt and a pair of khaki shorts?
Go as that hunky fashion-impaired private eye played by Tom Selleck
back in the '80s.
</P>
<P>
   _ Monk: If you have a brown or black hooded robe, wrap it up and
bow your head. Wear brown sandals, and you're ready.
</P>
<P>
   _ Art museum: Hang two prints of famous paintings around your
neck _ one on the front and one on the back _ and put on a little
cap with a sign pointing the way to the restrooms, the gift shop
and the cafe.
</P>
<P>
   _ Beatnik: Ah, the '50s coffeehouse scene. Wear black leggings
or stretch pants and a black turtleneck sweater. Add dark glasses,
a beret and bongos.
</P>
<P>
   _ Artist: Wear a man's dress shirt with the tails out, a beret
and a mustache drawn with an eye liner pencil. Add a palette (made
out of cardboard, aluminum foil and marking pens) and paint brush
to hold.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gold medalist: Wear a matching sweats outfit with foil medals
dangling from ribbons around your neck. Carry a small American flag
and bouquet of flowers.
</P>
<P>
   _ '50s gal: Wear a poodle skirt if you have one, or roll up your
jeans to the knees. Wear bobby socks and oxfords, or white anklets
and black flats. Top with a man's white dress shirt worn untucked,
and bring a pen for guests to write their name and slogans like
``Daddy-O'' on your shirt. Put your hair in a pony tail, wear red
lipstick, and chew bubble gum.
</P>
<P>
   _ Tofu: Get a box large enough to wear, cut out head and arm
holes, wrap it in white paper, and go to the party as tofu.
</P>
<P>
   _ Cloudy day: Wear a light blue sweat shirt and sweat pants with
cotton balls glued on it. And carry a squirt gun. When asked what
you are, say, ``I'm partly cloudy with a chance of showers.'' Then
start squirting.
</P>
<P>
   _ Hippie: Anything from the '60s and early '70s (or now), that
includes patched jeans, ponchos, Apache-style headbands over hair
combed with a center part. Add strands of beads, and lots of rings,
then draw a peace sign on your cheek. Go barefoot or wear any
rugged, earthy sandals.
</P>
<P>
   _ Wood nymph: Remember ``Midsummer Night's Dream,'' and slip
into an earthy or metallic-colored slip dress (think ethereal) with
flowers in your hair and lots of body glitter. Go barefoot or wear
sandals, and carry a branch you snipped off a tree or bush for a
woodsy prop.
</P>
<P>
   _ Geek: Wear khaki pants with a white dress shirt. Put a bunch
of mechanical pencils and a slide rule in your shirt pocket. It
helps if the pants are cuffed ultra-short, above the ankles. Add
glasses and slick your hair down with a side part. A hard briefcase
('70s-style), and any items (compass, flashlight, screwdriver)
dangling from belt or belt loops are a plus.
</P>
<P>
   _ Mafia man: Wear a dark suit with black shirt and tie and black
shoes with those little tassels (very Italian). Add dark glasses
and slick your hair back with gel. &UR;  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
