<P>
   (NYT45) ELDORADO DOS CARAJAS, Brazil -- Oct. 28, 1999 --
BRAZIL-JUSTICE, 10-28 -- Three years ago, 19 landless farm workers
were killed in a confrontation with the police at this bend in a
highway in the southeastern Amazon. More than 1,500 people
witnessed the Para state military police open fire, and the
incident was filmed and shown on Brazilian television hundreds of
times. But such irrefutable proof has not helped bring to justice
those responsible for the deaths. (Larry Rohter/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT44) POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- Oct. 28, 1999 -- ECON-IMPACT,
10-28 -- New housing in Poughkeepsie. The government has developed
a new method for measuring economic growth, but the recent
prosperity still falls short of earlier booms. (Joyce Dopkeen/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT43) WASHINGTON -- Oct. 28, 1999 -- CONGRESS-SPEND-2, 10-28
-- House Majority Whip Tom Delay, R-Texas, second from left, jokes
with Rep. Dave Weldon, R-Fla., left, after the House passed
spending cuts legislation on Thursday. Republicans pushed the last
and biggest spending bill of fiscal 2000 through the House on
Thursday despite a promised veto by President Clinton, even as the
president abandoned efforts to overhaul Social Security and
Medicare for the year. (Stephen Crowley/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
