-- TEACH-HOSPITALS, 10-28 -- To help cut costs, Mount Zion Hospital
in San Francisco will end in-patient and emergency room services.
Rank-and-file doctors, nurses and technicians at the hospitals say
they get little or no chance to contribute suggestions or influence
decisions on cuts. (Peter DaSilva/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
