<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TEAMSTERS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EX-TEAMSTERS OFFICIAL IS ACCUSED OF GRAFT  
(DW)
</HEADLINE>
   By STEVEN GREENHOUSE   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   A board of federal monitors Thursday charged a top lieutenant of
Ron Carey, the former Teamsters Union president, with embezzling
more than $12,500 and with breaching his fiduciary duty to union
members.
</P>
<P>
   The board, called the Independent Review Board, asked the
union's president, James P. Hoffa, to pursue disciplinary
proceedings that could lead to a fine against the official, Joseph
A. Padellaro. Padellaro resigned from the union in May, so he
cannot be suspended or expelled.
</P>
<P>
   For years, Carey relied heavily on Padellaro to clean up locals
that had been placed into trusteeship because of corrupt
leadership. Padellaro was often called Carey's ``super-trustee,''
because he was trustee over nine different Teamsters locals.
</P>
<P>
   The review board accused Padellaro of repeated double-dipping,
specifically of having purchased airplane tickets that were paid
for by the parent union and then asking various locals to reimburse
him for the trips.
</P>
<P>
   Padellaro's attorney, James Roth, denied all the accusations. He
said he was waiting to see the board's exhibits, detailing the
reimbursements to Padellaro, before he commented further.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
