<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Friday, Oct. 29. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
MEXICO-FEE _ Responding to criticism from U.S. lawmakers, the
Mexican government canceled plans Thursday to begin charging U.S.
tourists deposits of up to $800 to drive a car into the Mexican
interior. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
DEBATE (Hanover, N.H.) _ Republican presidential candidates squared
off on Thursday in what was for the most part a civilized debate
that turned tense at the mention of the candidate who wasn't there
_ Texas Gov. George W. Bush. By KRIS MAYES. Story will move in the
``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
ROSE-EDIT _ The biggest mistake NBC reporter Jim Gray made when he
interviewed Pete Rose at the World Series was assuming that a
sentimental public, overwrought with dewy emotion at the ``return''
of Rose to the scene of a Major League event, cared about the
facts. Story will move in the ``K'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
TV-GOODY (Undated) _ He's the king of the ``B'' movie, filling the
screen with monsters and cleavage aplenty. Now Roger Corman hosts
Monsterfest over Halloween weekend on American Movie Classics. By
BILL GOODYKOONTZ. Story will move in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
